verses.text_plain: I said in mine heart, Go to now, I will prove thee with mirth, therefore enjoy pleasure: and, behold, this also is vanity.
verses.verse_html: 1I said in mine heart, Go to now, I will prove thee with mirth, therefore enjoy pleasure: and, behold, this also is vanity.

verses.text_plain: I said of laughter, It is mad: and of mirth, What doeth it?
verses.verse_html: 2I said of laughter, It is mad: and of mirth, What doeth it?

verses.text_plain: I sought in mine heart to give myself unto wine, yet acquainting mine heart with wisdom; and to lay hold on folly, till I might see what was that good for the sons of men, which they should do under the heaven all the days of their life.
verses.verse_html:
3I sought in mine heart to give myself unto wine, yet acquainting mine heart with wisdom; and to lay hold on folly, till I might see what was that good for the sons of men, which they should do under the heaven all the days of their life. ▼
▼ to give…: Heb. to draw my flesh with wine
 , ▼
▼ all…: Heb. the number of the days of their life

footnotes.body_text: ▼ to give…: Heb. to draw my flesh with wine
footnotes.body_html: ▼ to give…: Heb. to draw my flesh with wine

footnotes.body_text: ▼ all…: Heb. the number of the days of their life
footnotes.body_html: ▼ all…: Heb. the number of the days of their life

verses.text_plain: I made me great works; I builded me houses; I planted me vineyards:
verses.verse_html: 4I made me great works; I builded me houses; I planted me vineyards:

verses.text_plain: I made me gardens and orchards, and I planted trees in them of all kind of fruits:
verses.verse_html: 5I made me gardens and orchards, and I planted trees in them of all kind of fruits:

verses.text_plain: I made me pools of water, to water therewith the wood that bringeth forth trees:
verses.verse_html: 6I made me pools of water, to water therewith the wood that bringeth forth trees:

verses.text_plain: I got me servants and maidens, and had servants born in my house; also I had great possessions of great and small cattle above all that were in Jerusalem before me:
verses.verse_html:
7I got me servants and maidens, and had servants born in my house; also I had great possessions of great and small cattle above all that were in Jerusalem before me: ▼
▼ servants born…: Heb. sons of my house

tokens.text: above all that were in Jerusalem

footnotes.body_text: ▼ servants born…: Heb. sons of my house
footnotes.body_html: ▼ servants born…: Heb. sons of my house

verses.text_plain: I gathered me also silver and gold, and the peculiar treasure of kings and of the provinces: I gat me men singers and women singers, and the delights of the sons of men, as musical instruments, and that of all sorts.
verses.verse_html:
8I gathered me also silver and gold, and the peculiar treasure of kings and of the provinces: I gat me men singers and women singers, and the delights of the sons of men, as musical instruments, and that of all sorts. ▼
▼ musical…: Heb. musical instrument and instruments

footnotes.body_text: ▼ musical…: Heb. musical instrument and instruments
footnotes.body_html: ▼ musical…: Heb. musical instrument and instruments

verses.text_plain: So I was great, and increased more than all that were before me in Jerusalem: also my wisdom remained with me.
verses.verse_html: 9So I was great, and increased more than all that were before me in Jerusalem: also my wisdom remained with me.

tokens.text: more than all that were before

verses.text_plain: And whatsoever mine eyes desired I kept not from them, I withheld not my heart from any joy; for my heart rejoiced in all my labour: and this was my portion of all my labour.
verses.verse_html: 10And whatsoever mine eyes desired I kept not from them, I withheld not my heart from any joy; for my heart rejoiced in all my labour: and this was my portion of all my labour.

verses.text_plain: Then I looked on all the works that my hands had wrought, and on the labour that I had laboured to do: and, behold, all was vanity and vexation of spirit, and there was no profit under the sun.
verses.verse_html: 11Then I looked on all the works that my hands had wrought, and on the labour that I had laboured to do: and, behold, all was vanity and vexation of spirit, and there was no profit under the sun.

verses.text_plain: And I turned myself to behold wisdom, and madness, and folly: for what can the man do that cometh after the king? even that which hath been already done.
verses.verse_html:
12And I turned myself to behold wisdom, and madness, and folly: for what can the man do that cometh after the king? even that which hath been already done. ▼
▼ even…: or, in those things which have been already done

footnotes.body_text: ▼ even…: or, in those things which have been already done
footnotes.body_html: ▼ even…: or, in those things which have been already done

verses.text_plain: Then I saw that wisdom excelleth folly, as far as light excelleth darkness.
verses.verse_html:
13Then I saw that wisdom excelleth folly, as far as light excelleth darkness. ▼
▼ that…: Heb. that there is an excellency in wisdom more than in folly, etc

footnotes.body_text: ▼ that…: Heb. that there is an excellency in wisdom more than in folly, etc
footnotes.body_html: ▼ that…: Heb. that there is an excellency in wisdom more than in folly, etc

verses.text_plain: The wise man’s eyes are in his head; but the fool walketh in darkness: and I myself perceived also that one event happeneth to them all.
verses.verse_html: 14The wise man’s eyes are in his head; but the fool walketh in darkness: and I myself perceived also that one event happeneth to them all.

verses.text_plain: Then said I in my heart, As it happeneth to the fool, so it happeneth even to me; and why was I then more wise? Then I said in my heart, that this also is vanity.
verses.verse_html:
15Then said I in my heart, As it happeneth to the fool, so it happeneth even to me; and why was I then more wise? Then I said in my heart, that this also is vanity. ▼
▼ happeneth even…: Heb. happeneth to me, even to me

tokens.text: and why was I then more

footnotes.body_text: ▼ happeneth even…: Heb. happeneth to me, even to me
footnotes.body_html: ▼ happeneth even…: Heb. happeneth to me, even to me

verses.text_plain: For there is no remembrance of the wise more than of the fool for ever; seeing that which now is in the days to come shall all be forgotten. And how dieth the wise man? as the fool.
verses.verse_html: 16For there is no remembrance of the wise more than of the fool for ever; seeing that which now is in the days to come shall all be forgotten. And how dieth the wise man? as the fool.

verses.text_plain: Therefore I hated life; because the work that is wrought under the sun is grievous unto me: for all is vanity and vexation of spirit.
verses.verse_html: 17Therefore I hated life; because the work that is wrought under the sun is grievous unto me: for all is vanity and vexation of spirit.

verses.text_plain: Yea, I hated all my labour which I had taken under the sun: because I should leave it unto the man that shall be after me.
verses.verse_html:
18Yea, I hated all my labour which I had taken under the sun: because I should leave it unto the man that shall be after me. ▼
▼ taken: Heb. laboured

verses.text_plain: And who knoweth whether he shall be a wise man or a fool? yet shall he have rule over all my labour wherein I have laboured, and wherein I have shewed myself wise under the sun. This is also vanity.
verses.verse_html: 19And who knoweth whether he shall be a wise man or a fool? yet shall he have rule over all my labour wherein I have laboured, and wherein I have shewed myself wise under the sun. This is also vanity.

tokens.text: whether he shall be a wise
and wherein I have shewed myself wise

verses.text_plain: Therefore I went about to cause my heart to despair of all the labour which I took under the sun.
verses.verse_html: 20Therefore I went about to cause my heart to despair of all the labour which I took under the sun.

verses.text_plain: For there is a man whose labour is in wisdom, and in knowledge, and in equity; yet to a man that hath not laboured therein shall he leave it for his portion. This also is vanity and a great evil.
verses.verse_html:
21For there is a man whose labour is in wisdom, and in knowledge, and in equity; yet to a man that hath not laboured therein shall he leave it for his portion. This also is vanity and a great evil. ▼
▼ leave: Heb. give

verses.text_plain: For what hath man of all his labour, and of the vexation of his heart, wherein he hath laboured under the sun?
verses.verse_html: 22For what hath man of all his labour, and of the vexation of his heart, wherein he hath laboured under the sun?

verses.text_plain: For all his days are sorrows, and his travail grief; yea, his heart taketh not rest in the night. This is also vanity.
verses.verse_html: 23For all his days are sorrows, and his travail grief; yea, his heart taketh not rest in the night. This is also vanity.

verses.text_plain: There is nothing better for a man, than that he should eat and drink, and that he should make his soul enjoy good in his labour. This also I saw, that it was from the hand of God.
verses.verse_html:
24There is nothing better for a man, than that he should eat and drink, and that he should make his soul enjoy good in his labour. This also I saw, that it was from the hand of God. ▼
▼ should make…: or, delight his senses

footnotes.body_text: ▼ should make…: or, delight his senses
footnotes.body_html: ▼ should make…: or, delight his senses

verses.text_plain: For who can eat, or who else can hasten hereunto, more than I?
verses.verse_html: 25For who can eat, or who else can hasten hereunto, more than I?

verses.text_plain: For God giveth to a man that is good in his sight wisdom, and knowledge, and joy: but to the sinner he giveth travail, to gather and to heap up, that he may give to him that is good before God. This also is vanity and vexation of spirit.
verses.verse_html:
26For God giveth to a man that is good in his sight wisdom, and knowledge, and joy: but to the sinner he giveth travail, to gather and to heap up, that he may give to him that is good before God. This also is vanity and vexation of spirit. ▼
▼ in his…: Heb. before him

footnotes.body_html: ▼ in his…: Heb. before him
